description:
&lt;p&gt;Do something amazing and join our team of remarkable people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Registered Nurses to join our highly skilled and motivated Bank Team, working at Cannock Hospital across:.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outpatients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Elective ward – Orthopedic and Rehabilitation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Temporary Staffing Bank Team is a friendly dedicated group of staff based on site here at The Royal Wolverhampton NHS Trust. The aim of the team is to ensure that Wards and Departments are never understaffed. They do this by ensuring that there is a pool of ‘Bank’ staff to call on who want to do extra shifts or temporary work. Temporary Staffing Bank workers are:- Staff that are available to be called on to work in a flexible capacity to fill a temporary vacancy or staffing shortfall. This type of work is carried out under the understanding of No Mutuality of Obligation. The Temporary Staffing Bank provides temporary cover for Wards, Departments, and Community services on a daily basis. Bank Workers may be required to cover any short-term staff shortages. Therefore Bank workers can be called to work anytime from a few days or hours’ notice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits of joining the Bank Flexibility&lt;/strong&gt; – you can work hours to suit your personal needs &lt;strong&gt;Excellent Rates of Pay including Enhanced Pay for Unsociable hours&lt;/strong&gt; Accrual of paid Annual leave (for Bank Workers only) Opportunity to work across a variety of areas Induction, Training and Development opportunities The Temporary Staffing Bank provides comprehensive support from recruitment to booking your first shift. You will be given a comprehensive induction and will have the opportunity to access training to support and further your career. So if you are a Registered Nurse, with accident and emergency experience there has never been a better time to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are able to view and book your shifts online or via Me App allowing for easy access to shifts on a first come first serve basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value the skills and experience you would bring to RWT to further enhance the already high standard of care that we deliver to the patients and their families&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Resourcing Team Tel: 01902 695443/695445&lt;/p&gt;
